  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across most operating conditions but inherent variability in one validation activity was assessed qualitatively rather than through a structured UQ protocol, leaving the hasUncertaintyQuantification link absent for that result. Full 13-factor assessment completed.",
