      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-rise validation across five operating conditions",
      "description": "Predicted hydraulic head compared to bench measurements across all five flow-speed combinations. Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition uncertainty and fluid viscosity variability yields 95% prediction intervals; all intervals bracket measured values within 8% relative error.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/cou2-mc-pressure-uq"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cou2-vr-03-hemolysis-index-validation",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — off-design high-shear condition",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared to in-vitro measurements at the off-design high-shear operating point (3 L/min, 3500 rpm). Inherent biological variability in erythrocyte fragility across donor blood samples was assessed qualitatively by the experimental team and noted in the test report; however, no structured uncertainty quantification node was linked to this validation result because the inter-donor variability was judged to be characterised sufficiently by narrative discussion. The aleatory component of hemolysis measurement scatter therefore remains uncharacterized in the structured evidence package."
    },
